FBIS4-40690 "drsov118_t_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Broadcasting Council Elects Chairman, Deputy Broadcasting Council Elects Chairman, Deputy LD1706110094 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1000 GMT 17 Jun 94 LD1706110094 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network Estonian BFN [Text] The Broadcasting Council met today for the first time. Rein Veidemann, deputy chairman of parliament's cultural commission, was elected its chairman, and Toivo Tasa, editor-in-chief of the VIKERKAAR magazine, was elected his deputy. One of the council's primary tasks is to appoint directors general for Estonian Radio and Estonian Television, within the next six months, to introduce a procedure for broadcasting advertisements and election campaigns and to define the conditions for the use of transmitters. The council must also endorse the constitutions for both Estonian Radio and Estonian Television.
